"n.废除，革除 【英】 n. 废除，革除(abolishi ng or being abolished) 【考】 abolitionist: slavery / anarchist: government(废奴主义者不要奴隸 制 / 无政府主义者不要政 府)反义词: persist in salvery(坚持奴隸制) 【记】 由动词abolish(废除) 而来 【同】 派生词: abolitionist(n. 废奴主义者) 【例】 the abolition of slavery n. 废除, 特指废除奴隸制度 【例】the abolition of slavery 废止奴隸制 【源】源于动词abolish(v 废除) 【反】persist in slavery(坚持奴隸制) 【记】音：暴力式，采取用暴力方式革命→废除(社会制度)；polish， 弄光；demolish : tear down,destroy abolition (n.)  1520s, from Middle French abolition or directly from Latin abolitionem (nominative abolitio) ""an abolition,"" noun of action from past participle stem of abolere ""destroy"" (see abolish). Specific application to ""opposition to the black slave trade as a political question"" is first attested 1788."
